{
  "stem": "16442.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 309.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We tried to help them as much as we could.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But somehow, because of my father's position, we never thought that it could happen to us.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We heard about Hitler.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And [? oh, ?] news was very hard to get because we weren't allowed to listen to radios.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the only way we used to get news, some people would listen to the BBC late at night and come to the synagogue and tell it to the other people.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So when my father came home from the synagogue, the first question was always, so what's new?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What did you hear in the synagogue?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not really, for two reason.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "First of all, my father was a special person who had special privileges.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And second of all, my mother got sick, so it was very difficult.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We never thought about leaving.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We always thought that my father's privileges will protect us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] Well, it's very difficult to say because somebody who really wants to make plans in one's life was interrupted with the bitterness of anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They never could think of the future, never knew what will happen tomorrow because not only the Nazis were all over, but the Hungarians took over their customs.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they became very anti-Semitic, and they had special-- like [? all ?] the Iron Guards, and they were also beating up Jews.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So at that time, we had only one thing to think of, hoping that tomorrow will be a better future and we'll be able to think of the future.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, definitely.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, don't forget, I was only 16, 17 years old, and things were really bad.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were just hoping that this will go away like a bad dream and then normal life will come back.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
